title: 1 Bed Flat, Westminster Bridge Road, SE1
description: I am proud to present to the lettings market this highly specified, contemporary and unique one bedroom apartment located on Westminster Bridge Road. The communal areas are well maintained with a tiled entrance and carpet to the landings. On site facilities to the development include lift access to all floors and a cycling storage area.The interior of the property has been thoughtfully designed and finished throughout to cover all aspects of modern day living. Benefits to this apartment are plentiful and include an abundance of luxury fittings including underfloor heating to the engineered wood flooring and downlights to all main areas. The integrated stainless steel appliances are set within polished stone counter tops with under cupboard worktop lighting. Open plan to the kitchen is the bright and spacious living space with exceptionally large double glazed windows to maximise the natural flow of light in to the room. The living and kitchen has been carefully arranged to utilise the space perfectly giving the feeling of a separate areas whilst remaining open plan. The ceramic tiled bathroom includes a modern three piece suite, complete with a heated towel rail and a shower over the bath. Lastly, the double bedroom with plenty of storage options including a walk in closet and built in mirrored double wardrobe, has been finished with electric underfloor heating to the matching engineered flooring found throughout the apartment.

description: Fantastic 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom flat with small balcony from living room, in a great location. The apartment has just been redecorated and is very clean & fresh.The apartment features large double glazed windows throughout.The living room has floor to ceiling windows and opens onto a small balcony.The entire apartment has a lovely bright and open aspect.The modern oak flooring and solid oak furniture creates a feeling of calm.The living room features a smart looking sofa bed, a circular oak and glass table and a TV on an ultra adjustable bracket so it can be viewed from the sofa, table or kitchen.The view from the living room is very open and encompasses the trees of Coram's Fields and the attractive architecture of the University post graduate accommodation. The bedroom now includes 2 matching solid oak double wardrobes and large solid oak chest of drawers providing plenty of storage.The oak bed is king sized and designed to allow underbed storage of suitcases etc.The bathroom includes a large walk in shower. The amount of furniture can flexed in accordance with the tenants wishes.The fully fitted units in the kitchen include a dishwasher, fridge with freezer compartment, microwave and washer/dryer. The apartment is located on the 3rd floor, with lift.The apartment is quiet and the bedroom at the rear very quiet indeed.There are many delightful garden squares around the apartment - title: 2 Bed Maisonette, Colnbrook Street, SE1
description: An outstanding Grade II Listed two bedroom maisonette. Set in SE1, this location is excellent, with close proximity to London Bridge and Southbank. The location offers superb transport links and a fantastic selection of local amenities in the surrounding area. ColnbrookStreet is between St Georges Road and London Road, which is just off Gladstone Street. This location has always beenpopular, however now even more so, with the SE1 regeneration happening on its doorstep. DESCRIPTIONUpon entry, the reception room on the left has lovely wooden flooring, a cast iron radiator, high ceilings and a large sashwindow with shutters overlooking the street. The ornate fireplace with marble surround acts as a focal point for theroom. Both sides of the fireplace have fitted alcoves with shelving and there are bi-folding doors leading into the kitchenarea. The kitchen also has high ceilings with cornicing, wooden flooring and plenty of space for a large dining table and chairs.The work surfaces are made from composite stone and you will also find all the latest appliances including an oven, gashob, microwave, dishwasher, sink and an inset fridge and freezer. There are views of the garden below vialarge sash windows. The bathroom is also on the raised ground floor and is situated at the rear of the flat. Here there is awet room, separate bath, extractor fan, heated towel rail and frosted sash windows. The hallway provides under stairstorage, great for neatly tucking away various household goods. Up a flight of stairs to the half landing, there is access to a south-east facing roof terrace, which is ideal for al-frescodining or simply to enjoy a morning coffee. The two bedrooms are located on the first floor. Bedroom one has two large sash windows with shutters, woodenflooring, a fireplace with fitted alcoves to each side, built-in storage and plenty of space for a double bed. Bedroom twohas built-in shelving, space for a double bed and delightful views of the garden below. Here you also have plenty of roomfor storage.DIRECTIONS Elephant & Castle Stations (Zone 1/2) (National Rail, Northern & Bakerloo Line) is approximately 0.4 miles away.Waterloo Stations (National Rail, Northern, Bakerloo, Waterloo & City & Jubilee Line) are approximately 0.6 miles away.The area is also well served by a frequent bus service into Central London and beyond and a number of SantanderDocking Stations can also be found close by.Furnishing: The tenants can have the choice of full furnishing, however this will increase the rent slightly per month.

Regent Street, Oxford Street, Knightsbridge, Kensington (for The Natural History and V & A Museums, etc), Hyde Park (for the many festivals and shows, etc, throughout the yearâ¦including The Winter Wonderland around Christmas time), The Tower of London, The South Bank Centre, including The Hayward Gallery, The National Theatre and Royal Festival Hall are also close by, as are the IMAX cinema at Waterloo, the National Film Museum, Shakespeareâs Globe, The Imperial War Museum, The Tate Modern, Trafalgar Square, Buckingham Palace, The Royal Opera House and The Coliseum, Covent Garden and Theatre & Film Land around Leicester Square, on the Strand as well as on Shaftsbury Avenue, etc, in the West Endâ¦ and letâs not forget the City of Londonâ¦the financial heart (and brain) of the U. K.! I could go onâ¦   Sport: A Gym, just 3 â 5 minutesâ walk away on the Walworth Road, and now also at the NEW Elephant & Castle Leisure Centre (12 â 15 minutesâ walk away), are open 24 hours. Thereâs very cheap (sometimes freeâ¦) swimming as well at Camberwell Leisure Centre (just 12 - 15 minutesâ walk in the other direction - towards Camberwell Green). Thereâs also a Rock-Climbing wall at Vauxhall (under the railway arches) as well as, of course, the world famous Oval Cricket Ground close by (between Vauxhall, Kennington and Camberwell).   More about The Elephant & Castle (just 12 â 15 minutesâ walk away): FYI, over the next few years, the Elephant & Castle will become London's most exciting new neighbourhood in a Â£1.5bn transformation that will evolve and enhance its identity. It will very soon become known as âthe place to beâ rather than just âa place to pass throughâ.   Already a lively London neighbourhood, The Elephant & Castle offers all the convenience of a Zone 1 location. Known affectionately to the locals as 'The Elephant', the area has a rich history stretching back to medieval timesâ¦and so much more to offer residents, visitors, and investors, etc, alike.   Located in a prime position in the heart of (south) central London, The Elephant & Castle is an excellent transport hub, with a Mainline Train station (direct trains to Kings Cross, Luton, Gatwick Airport and Brighton), a Zone 1 Tube station, of course, and links to nearly 50 different Bus routes. Fast and frequent London Underground services connect you to the whole of London via the Northern and Bakerloo lines.   Once all the main infrastructure projects have been completed, The Elephant & Castle will become one of the first fully Internet and social media friendly residential neighbourhoods in the whole of London.   GETTING AROUND:   The property is also, approximately, 15 - 20 minutesâ walk (5 - 10 minutes by bus & 7 - 10 minutes by bike) away from the Elephant & Castle Underground and Overground Stations, with their fast connections to anywhere you can think of in London and beyond.    The property is also served by a myriad of day and night buses stopping nearby (approx. 2 minutesâ walk in either direction). They can also get you quickly to where you need to be.   There are various âpedalâ bike stations 5 â 7 mins walk away (approx), with several others all along the Walworth Road up to the Elephant & Castle station. There are many cycle routes to choose from, including the CS7.   Parking: If required, Parking Permits can be applied for through the Southwark Council website.   On Foot: FYI, Borough Market is around 25 mins away, London Bridge about 30 mins, The South Bank is approximately 40 mins away, Covent Garden and Leicester Squareâ¦ 50 mins, Euston, St. Pancras, and Kingâs Cross stationsâ¦just over an hour (each).

description: Offering breathtaking views of the iconic Shard, this residence is a haven for those seeking a stylish and entertaining-friendly property. This prime location offers excellent accessibility, with residents enjoying leisurely walks across Tower Bridge into the city or utilizing the efficient transport links available. London Bridge Mainline Station provides access to underground services via the Jubilee and Northern lines, while Tower Hill offers connections via the District and Circle lines. title: 2 Bed Flat, Rufford Street, N1
description: Key features* Stunning 2 Double Bedroom/ 2 Bathroom Duplex Flat - only available to rent as a whole property (2 bedrooms)* Gated Mews Development Setting* Heart Of King's Cross Location* Luxury Accommodation With Stylish Interiors* Private Balcony* Superb Open Plan Reception/Kitchen/Diner* Contemporary Bathroom And Master En-Suite* Off Street Parking* Moments From Transport Links And Vibrant AmenitiesStunning two double bedroom, two bathroom, luxury duplex apartment with a parking space directly outside its own private entrance, enviably situated within a gated mews in the heart of King's Cross, moments from fashionable Granary Square and Coal Drops Yard. The property has been superbly decorated and furnished, offering bright and spacious accommodation over two floors, with stylish interiors and a high spec finish throughout. Features include an impressive open plan reception/kitchen and newly fitted breakfast bar area, private balcony, master bedroom with dressing area and en-suite, contemporary style family bathroom, newly installed balcony doors, double glazing and electric vehicle charger. Rufford Mews is a quiet gated cul-de-sac, a few minutes walk from the ever-evolving Kings Cross, Granary Square & Coal Drops Yard. This vibrant location provides a multitude of shops and amenities and an array of fashionable bars, restaurants and cafes. Also home to the brand new headquarters for Google, Facebook, YouTube, The Guardian & Central Saint Martin's. Barnsbury Conservation Area is just as close which is one of the most revered locations in Islington, traditional gastro pubs along with some more cutting edge offerings closer to Upper Street. It is this mix of traditional English charm on the doorstep of the bustle and international flavours of Kings Cross which lend the area much of its appeal. Presented in good condition, it is in a premium block in the heart of Shad Thames with a balcony and parking. Tenancy: The Flat will be available to move into from September 4th 2023 Viewings: We will be hosting viewings in August 2023 and we'd advise contacting us as soon as possible to book a viewing.SituationShad Thames is a desirable location along the banks of the River Thames, steeped in history and enchanting character. A variety of bars and restaurants are within walking distance. The area is very accessible and whilst many residents walk across Tower Bridge into the City, there are also good transport links via London Bridge main line train station and underground (Jubilee and Northern line) and Tower Hill (Circle and District line) - an additional transport option is the River Taxi at St Katharine Docks.

title: 1 Bed Flat, Victor Cazalet House, N1
description: Short let of a 1 double bedroom 1st floor flat with separate kitchen and sitting room superbly located in the heart of Islington. Accommodation comprises separate reception room with electric fire, kitchen, bathroom and 1 double bedroom with small built-in wardrobe and access to a balcony with views onto St Marys Church Gardens. The flat is unfurnished. Please note, this flat will be put up for sale in August. Hence, it is suitable for anyone looking to rent only for a few months until the sale goes through.The flat has been finished to a high standard throughout. A modern bathroom and kitchen (equipped with fridge/freezer, dishwasher, washing machine, microwave, hob/oven), the sitting room is dual aspect, the balcony has been fitted with weather treated decking and there is plenty of storage throughout. Located between Upper Street and Essex Road, the property affords superb access to the wide ranging amenities that Upper Street has to offer. Islington Green is moments away along with all of the bars, shops and restaurants of Upper St on your door step. Gaskin Street is superbly located for access to the transport links of Angel Station (Northern Line), Highbury & Islington (Victoria Line and Overground Network), Essex Road (National Rail) and bus routes providing access to the City, West End and all across London. Street parking is possible with a resident permit.

title: 1 Bed Flat, Latchmere Road, SW11
description: Welcome to this charming and elegant one-bedroom apartment in the heart of Battersea, located in a unique and exclusive development with private access from the street. Situated near the picturesque Battersea Park, the vibrant Clapham Junction, the iconic Albert Bridge, and the fashionable Chelsea, this residence offers a prime location in a beautiful residential area. Upon stepping into the apartment, you are greeted with an abundance of natural light streaming through large windows, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. The spacious living area is thoughtfully designed, providing ample room for relaxation and entertaining guests. The modern and stylish interior decor complements the apartment's contemporary feel, offering a perfect blend of comfort and sophistication. The bedroom is a peaceful sanctuary, exuding tranquility and comfort, allowing you to unwind and escape the hustle and bustle of city life. It offers a cozy retreat with ample storage space and a relaxing ambiance that ensures a restful night's sleep. The kitchen boasts state-of-the-art appliances and ample counter space, making it a delight for culinary enthusiasts, complete with newly fitted cabinets and dishwasher. What sets this apartment apart is the exclusive development, ensuring privacy and security. With a private entrance from the street, you'll feel like you're entering your own oasis in the heart of the city. The location of this apartment is ideal for those seeking the best of both worlds. While it offers a peaceful and picturesque residential area, it also boasts excellent local amenities. From charming cafes and trendy restaurants to boutique shops and convenient grocery stores, everything you need is just a stone's throw away. The newly fitted bathroom includes a walk in shower and spacious bath.With several roof lights and bi-fold doors opening onto the garden this light filled property would suit a small family, couple or single professional looking for easy access to the City and West End and to the bars and restaurants of Fulham and nearby Kings Road, Parson's Green and more. The Area:Fulham is a vibrant and affluent town located in the southwestern part of London. It is known for its desirable residential areas, picturesque streets, and a thriving community. One of the notable features of Fulham is its proximity to the River Thames. The riverside walkways and parks provide stunning views of the water and create opportunities for recreational activities, picnics, and leisurely strolls.Sports enthusiasts will appreciate Fulham's connection to football, Craven Cottage Stadium and Stamford Bridge, the home of Fulham and Chelsea respectively. Nature lovers can enjoy the nearby green spaces, including Bishops Park, Fulham Palace Gardens, and Hurlingham Park. Fulham also offers a diverse range of dining and shopping options. The town is dotted with numerous trendy cafes, restaurants, and bars where visitors can indulge in a variety of cuisines and enjoy a vibrant nightlife. The area also offers proximity to other popular attractions in London, such as the Natural History Museum, Victoria and Albert Museum, and Kensington Gardens.

title: Room in a Shared House, Double En-Suite, N4
description: Price includes utility bills (water, WIFI, electric and heating)Price stated is based on a 10-12 month agreement, based on a single occupant. Room not suitable for couples. Shorter rental periods considered. Message us for more info!This double en-suite room is located in a Finsbury Park property on the first floor at the front of the building.Meet Gravity Co-living Finsbury Park, a charming Victorian townhouse with a modern twist, offering move-in-ready en-suite double bedrooms and large communal areas including stylish lounge, kitchens, dining area, landscaped gardens and co-working - perfect for rest, work and play. Move in and meet like-minded people, explore London with locals and enjoy complimentary events such as fitness sessions, workshops, social drinks, quiz nights, community dinners, breakfast club and so much more.The spaceThe home from the front is a large sustainable Victorian Townhouse, with solar panels and green roof for micro-development. From the back we have a small modern block separated from the Victorian townhouse with large landscaped gardens with seating areas, secure bike storage and BBQ equipment - perfect for the summer months!LoungeAs you enter into the front of the home, to your right is a stylish communal lounge area with sofas, bean bags and chairs. We have a big flat screen TV so you can watch your favourite shows, a wide variety of games to play, or some books for you to read. This is a space you relax, unwind and meet some incredible people.Co-workingTo the left is a large desk area used as a co-working area in the day. Come and meet other professionals to increase your network. The property has free coffee machines for you to use throughout the day. At night, this space becomes available for community events such as dinners.RoomsOnce you arrive at your room, expect a cosy en-suite with a double bed. You'll find a good amount of storage space in each room as well as your very own fridge! You'll also have your own en-suite bathroom with showers - perfect for those self-care nights.NeighbourhoodFinsbury Park is a vibrant, cosmopolitan area with a real sense of local community and everything you need on your doorstep. With a calm social scene you can relax, while just being a short 20 minutes from the city centre via public transport. The area has a growing cafe culture and a number of cozy pubs such as Common Ground, La Fabric and The White Lion. Just 1 minute walk from this home is the park itself, spanning a huge 46 hectares. The park offers copious amounts of green space, sports grounds, tennis courts and a serene boating lake - perfect for picnics and long walks. In the summer months the park is used for festivals such as Wireless Festival with acts like Kayne West and Drake.Close to Finsbury park is also the Parkland Walk - a 3.1 mile linear green route which follows the course of an old railway track running between Finsbury Park, Alexandra Palace, Stroud Green, Crouch End, Highgate and Muswell Hill. Take a 15 minutes walk to Woodberry Wetlands to explore the nature reserve or head 10 minutes to Clissold Park most known for the birds, goats and a herd of fallow deer.Getting aroundSay goodbye to long commutes. Finsbury Park is close to all key business hubs in London. Finsbury Park is connected by the Victoria and Piccadilly Line, which connects to Kings Cross in 8 minutes, Victoria in 16 minutes and Canary Wharf in 30. Finsbury Park also has the over ground and rail links making it one of the most connected areas in central London.Please note, some items shown in photos are for marketing purposes only. please note, there are 34 rooms in total in this property. The landlord is only able to put up to 12 above. Price shown is based on a single occupant only.

title: 2 Bed Flat, Trinder Road, N19
description: This charming flat occupies the upper half of a terraced house on a quiet residential street located equidistant between Crouch End and Stroud Green. The local area is a genuinely wonderful part of London: within 15 minutes you can be in Finsbury Park, Alexandra Palace, Priory Park, Queen's Wood, Highgate Wood, or the Parkland Walk for space and exercise; in the bars and restaurants of Crouch End and the Stroud Green Road for a night out; at the Art House or Picturehouse to watch a film; or at the Park Road lido for an open air swim. The area is still full of independent, interesting businesses, and there are a number of excellent food produce shops -- whether delicatessens, fruit and veg sellers, or butchers.The W7 bus leaves from the end of the road, and arrives at Finsbury Park station within eight minutes; from there, the Victoria and Piccadilly Lines head into the middle of town, and there are trains heading direct into the City (Moorgate 14 minutes), and even direct to Gatwick Airport. The flat is also situated very near to Crouch Hill overground station, which is useful for getting up to Walthamstow, and to destinations in the west of London like Richmond and Kew.          The flat is bright and spacious, and presents a calm, understated and modern feel. It has been renovated and maintained to a very high standard over the past five years. There are wooden floors throughout, with a solid oak parquet that was recently laid in the lower half of the flat changing into elegantly painted floorboards in the upstairs bedroom. All the windows in the flat are sashes, which have been renovated and double-glazed within the last four years. The heart of the flat is a combined open-plan kitchen, dining area and living room. The kitchen has an induction hob, single oven, fridge / freezer and Bosch clothes washer / dryer. The three-sided kitchen surface is very generous for food preparation, and could also double as a breakfast bar. Next to the kitchen, the wide open room could simply be used as a very spacious living room; or -- as is the case currently -- divided into a dining area with ample space for a large dining table, next to a living area still with sufficient space for a sofa, armchairs and a sideboard.   The central stairway gives a real sense of flow to the flat, so that none of the rooms in the flat feel disconnected or remote. Despite that, the three distinct levels of the flat each retain a sense of privacy and self-sufficiency -- not least because each bedroom has its own separate bathroom.Heading up the staircase from the central living room, the main bedroom occupies the whole depth of house from front to back. The main feature of the bedroom is a distinctive painted brick chimney breast, next to which a beautiful ply-edged wardrobe has been custom-built, complete with oak veneer shelving for books and plants. In the same style as the wardrobe, a custom eaves storage unit runs the full width of the room and also provides some bed-side storage. Next to the back window that looks out over trees and gardens, there is plenty of room for a small office. The bedroom has its own bathroom, with full size bath, and more useful hidden eaves storage for larger items such as suitcases.Heading downstairs from the central living room, there is a second bedroom at the back of the flat, also with its own bathroom with a walk-in waterfall shower. The second bedroom is sufficiently spacious for an adult double bed and clothes storage or, as is currently the case, for two children's beds and equipment. Alternatively, this room could serve as a spacious and quiet office.In the front garden of the flat, there is a large Asgard metal bike storage shed that is exclusively for the use of the flat tenants.

title: 2 Bed Flat, Green Lanes, N4

description: PLEASE NOTE - THIS IS ONLY AVAILABLE FOR SHORT LET FOR THE MONTH OF AUGUST!Beautiful, top floor, one bed flat in a Victorian terraced house. There are two side tables, a chest of drawers for clothes storage and a bookshelf (we can leave or remove the books). The room has big windows which let in lots of natural light and can provide a welcome breeze on a hot day.
